---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Spring Cloud Stream
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- lightweight messaging-driven microservices framework
- based on Spring Integration and Spring Boot
- provides a declarative model for sending and receiving messages using
  RabbitMQ or Kafka

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Spring Cloud Stream features
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- decoupling of messaging between producers and consumers by creating bindings
  that can be used out of the box
- no need to write any broker specific code
- add the required binding dependencies to your application, and Spring Cloud
  Stream takes care of the messaging connectivity and communication

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Spring Cloud Stream Concepts
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Application Model - application communicates using input/output channels

# Binder abstraction - provides at the Kafka and RabbitMQ binder implementations

# Persistent Publish/Subscribe

# Consumer Groups - concept for scalability

# Partitioning support - performance and consistency,
    ensure that common data is processed by the same consumer instances

# Binder API